						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅgachōḷa III. Date Lost.</p>						

						<p>This records the provision for the supply of one <hi rend="italic">uṟi</hi> of ghee measured by the <hi rend="italic">dēvar nāḻi</hi> for burning two perpetual lamps by Pokkākkuḍaiyār••••Iyaṟpagai-yāṇḍār•••• of Marukal-nāḍu. Iyaṟpagai, after whom the donor is named, was one of the śaiva devotees whose lives are narrated in the <hi rend="italic">Periyapurāṇam.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
